---------------------------------------------------------------------



object.fit:  to set the image accoding to parent div  width
img {
  object-fit: contain;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
}

fill: The image is resized to fill the entire container, even if it means losing its aspect ratio.


contain: The image is resized to fit within the container while maintaining its aspect ratio.

cover: The image is resized to cover the entire container while maintaining its aspect ratio. If the image is larger than the container, it will be cropped.

none: The image is not resized.
scale-down: The image is resized to fit within the container while maintaining its aspect ratio, but only if the image is larger than the container.


---------------------------------------------------------------------




flex-wrap: The flex-wrap property in CSS is used to specify whether a flex container should wrap its items onto multiple lines or not.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

transition: transition property is used to add animation to the element when it is hovered or clicked.
eg : transition: background-color 0.5s ease-in-out;
transition: property duration timing-function delay;
